Swap is for changing courses; it does not change discussion sections.

Options is for changing discussion sections, and it will not work if you are waitlisted.

Not sure if this works in your particular case but CalCentral has a "swap" command that will add a new class and drop an old class simultaneously. May not apply to discussion sections but it's worth a shot.

history.content: This depends on where you are on the waitlist for your sections, and if there are other sections with space full.

If the section you originally signed up for is full, I would switch to an open discussion section (would recommend sections 031/032 for LAB and 131/132, since they were just recently added and should have 20+ seats available). I don't believe there should be any more enrollment holds on 61C, so you should be able to enroll directly into the class by selecting an open section. Unfortunately, with the new registration system, if the section you signed up for is full, then people who signed up for a section that's still open will be enrolled off of the waitlist before you.

I'm currently waitlisted for 61c (have been since phase 1). I was position 16 on the waitlist yesterday, and only moved up to position 15. Should I stay as is, or should I switch into an open discussion section? The issue is calcentral isn't allowing me to swap sections for a waitlisted class, so I'd have to drop and then re-add the class. Is this worth doing or should I just stay in the current position on the waitlist?
